'''Louis J. Doctor''' is an [[e-commerce]] entrepreneur, and the founder of [[Crowd Supply]] and Velotech.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.wired.com/2015/04/one-companys-quest-save-crowdfunding-scammers-flakes/ |title=The Quest to Save Crowdfunding From Scammers and Flakes |publisher=WIRED |date=2015-04-06 |accessdate=2016-09-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/portland/morning_call/2013/03/how-a-portland-startup-does.html |title=Crowd Supply brings crowdfunding to manufacturing - Portland Business Journal |website=Web.archive.org |date= |accessdate=2016-09-11 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160423120853/http://www.bizjournals.com/portland/morning_call/2013/03/how-a-portland-startup-does.html |archivedate=2016-04-23 |df= }}</ref> He utilises an approach that has been called "reverse e-commerce".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/marc-ostrofsky/biketiresdirectcom-case-s_b_1075717.html |title=BikeTiresDirect.com... Case Study in 'Reverse E-Commerce,' Sell then Buy |publisher=Huffington Post |date=2012-01-07 |accessdate=2016-09-10}}</ref>

Doctor is also a managing director at [[Horizon Partners]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://horizonpartners.com/team/ |title=Team |publisher=Horizon Partners |date= |accessdate=2016-09-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchbase.com/person/lou-doctor |title=Lou Doctor - Managing Director @ Horizon Partners &#124; CrunchBase |website=Web.archive.org |date=2013-01-01 |accessdate=2016-09-11 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714014546/http://www.crunchbase.com/person/lou-doctor |archivedate=2014-07-14 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/Research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapid=139077043 |title=Horizon Partners: Private Company Information - Businessweek |website=Bloomberg.com |date= |accessdate=2016-09-10}}</ref>

