{{update|date=August 2016|note=all links are 404; is it cancelled?}} The '''Whirlwind wheelchair''' is a [[wheelchair]] designed to be made in [[developing countries]] using local resources, in a [[sustainable development]] effort.
It was co-designed by [[Ralf Hotchkiss]] of Whirlwind Wheelchair International. Hotchkiss, a paraplegic, has traveled extensively, designing wheelchairs that could be built in developing countries.
Whirlwind Wheelchair International uses the principle of [[open source design]],<ref>{{ cite web | title = OPEN SOURCE DESIGN | url = http://www.whirlwindwheelchair.org/open.htm }}</ref> and offers construction classes and consulting services.
